text: tell us how you really feel about kalmene <@U3MTJRAQL>
Look we all agree Boros is bad...looking at the legendary creatures in RtRtR WotC agrees too.
My problem has never been Kalemne! That designer did the best with what he was given after another idiot designer took his slice of the color pie

Yesterday
Asap

other than that i should have time to get it in
My biggest problem with Boros is never the weaknesses of the pair but a lack of interesting commanders
I can work around a weakness. I can't do shit with the fifth bad iteration of Angus Kro or the sixth bad iteration of Firemane Angel
And artificial design constraints. "red/white must always only ever be about attacking"
But even that would be okay if they tried to do it in an interesting way
They don't even try it seems like
I much rather build mono red than boros
in general i only build decks that have white as a tertiary color
ive never been happy with a half-white deck
They printed an uncommon simic commander in Dominaria of a character who is mentioned in one line in the first story that's better than any Boros mythic legend ever printed.
Basically every Boros commander is Ulrich and we’d like it to be Vildinpack Alpha instead
Tajic could’ve read UW: deal X damage to any target where X is the number of soldiers you control.
I mean....the flavor win.
Or RW: Tajic deal 1 damage to each creature and player.
Or how about some hasty draws?
Or he sunforgers?
They won’t give draws because RW doesn’t intersect there.
or whenever two other creatures attack he gets +5/+5
and ehes indestructible
It doesn't have to intersect. You're thinking hybrid.
He's multicolor.
Give him vigilance and hasty draws. There. Now he's red and white.
it would be nice if he tutored low power creatures into play
i think it wouldve been cool if they made them guild colors with a separate colored ability
that wouldve been neat
I’m just telling you how they’d answer that.
I can’t think of a RW card that does that kind of draw.
Or just staple Reconnaissance into Tajic.
They only answer that for boros though
When a slightly out of pie thing happens with other colors they rationalize why it is okay, with boros they rationalize why it's not

I mean,  you're not wrong that's what they'd say, it's just weird they seem so protective of their narrow boros definitions where as they almost look for ways to expand the concepts for other color pairs
I think because RW is so prevalent in Limited it would probably skew that experience. Who knows.
Maybe, but that doesn't explain their abject refusal to do anything interesting with it in edh

I'd love to be in the room and hear some of the discussions. Imagine when the Kalemne and Anya deck was presented. What was the reaction? Are they aware they keep doing the same shitty thing nobody likes?
Agreed. For example, while Daxos missed a bit on the power level at least it was interesting.

"Hey guys, we've got the new Tajic and Aurelia finished. Remember how we made them the first time and both were barely playable and fairly uninteresting? We've done less playable and less interesting versions of each."

That's the question I want someone on a show to just full-stop ask Gavin. "Do you think you guys are succeeding in making interesting Boros commanders, and if the answer is no then why the fuck do you keep giving us the same shitty combat damage reliant commanders set after set that aren't even particularly good at what they're supposed to do?"
"And if the answer is yes, what the fuck?"
Get Gavin on your show
